# Reference for Railway variables (copy values in the Railway dashboard; do not commit secrets).
#
# ── Deploy checklist (frontend 502 / favicon) ───────────────────────────────
# 1) Railway → frontend service → Settings → Build:
#    - Dockerfile path: Dockerfile   (repo root; auto-detected)
#    - Root directory: empty or /         (same folder as Dockerfile + serve-static.mjs)
# 2) Deployments → latest → Logs: must contain:
#      [static] boot: PORT=... dist=/app/dist
#      [static] listening on http://0.0.0.0:...
# 3) If those lines are missing, the container never bound PORT → edge returns 502.
#
# If deploy logs show nginx (/docker-entrypoint.sh, "nginx/1.x") you are NOT running this
# repo’s Node image — Railway used a stale cached build or never picked up the root Dockerfile.
# Fix: push latest main, then Redeploy → disable “use build cache” / clear build cache if offered.
#
# Production URLs (example)
# -----------------------
# Frontend: https://one-yield-production.up.railway.app
# Backend:  https://one-yield-backend-production.up.railway.app
#
# Railway variable references: the name inside ${{ ... }} MUST match your service slug
# exactly (Dashboard → service → Settings → name / reference). Example:
#   VITE_API_URL="${{one-yield-backend.RAILWAY_PUBLIC_DOMAIN}}"
# resolves to hostname only (no https://) — the app adds https:// automatically.
#
# Recommended: literal https URLs (avoids broken ${{...}} during Docker build):
#   VITE_API_URL=https://one-yield-backend-production.up.railway.app
#   VITE_WS_URL=https://one-yield-backend-production.up.railway.app
#
# PORT on the frontend: Railway often shows port 8080. Setting PORT=8080 in Variables is OK;
# serve-static.mjs listens on process.env.PORT (default 8080). Do not point the app at a
# different port than Railway forwards to.
#
# VITE_PUBLIC_URL is not used by this Vite app unless you add it to vite.config; safe to omit.
#
# Backend (one-yield-backend)
# ---------------------------
# Prefer letting Railway set PORT. If you set PORT=3001, ensure it matches what Railway’s
# proxy expects for that service, or remove it and use the injected PORT.
# DATABASE_URL: use Railway Postgres plugin reference ${{Postgres.DATABASE_URL}}
#
# CORS_ORIGIN (browser calls from the frontend):
#   https://one-yield-production.up.railway.app
# Or CORS_ORIGIN=* for permissive dev-style CORS.
#
# RPC_URL / FACTORY_ADDRESS / keys: match your Hedera testnet deployment.
#
# Frontend (one-yield-frontend) — build-time Vite vars
# -----------------------------------------------------
# VITE_API_URL (no trailing slash):
#   https://one-yield-backend-production.up.railway.app
#
# VITE_WS_URL (Socket.IO — same host as API; optional if frontend code falls back to VITE_API_URL):
#   https://one-yield-backend-production.up.railway.app
#
# If you use ${{ServiceName.RAILWAY_PUBLIC_DOMAIN}}, ensure ServiceName matches Railway exactly.
# Hostname-only values work; the app prepends https:// (http:// for localhost / 127.0.0.1).
